#include '../template.wml'

<latemp_subject "Solver and Generator for ABC Path" />

<set-var modname="Games-ABC_Path-Solver" />
<set-var sco_mod="http://search.cpan.org/dist/<get-var modname />/" />

<set-var gen_modname="Games-ABC_Path-Generator" />
<set-var gen_sco_mod="http://search.cpan.org/dist/<get-var gen_modname />/" />

<p>
The 
<a href="<get-var sco_mod />"><get-var modname /></a> Perl 5 CPAN distribution implements a solver for 
<a href="http://www.brainbashers.com/abcpath.asp">ABC Path</a> as featured on
brainbashers.com. It provides a standalone command-line “abc-path-solver”
program and an Application Programmer Interface (API).
</p>

<p>
The
<a href="<get-var gen_sco_mod />"><get-var gen_modname /></a> Perl 5 CPAN 
distribution implements a generator for ABC Path layouts based on a random 
number seed. What it does is first generate a random path through the 5*5
board, and then assigns the hints randomly. Sometimes the process takes a 
relatively long time to complete.
</p>

<p>
The BitBucket.org repository also contains a port of the code of the solver
and generator to JavaScript, which will hopefully allow it to be usable as
an in-browser game in the future.
</p>

<p>
Currently, documentation is a little lacking.
</p>

